=== EXPLORATION FINDINGS ===

Server Configuration:
- Default port: 3000 (configurable via PORT env var)
- Default DB URL: postgres://harness:harness@localhost:5432/remote_harness
- CORS: Permissive by default
- Worker stale timeout: 90 seconds
- Max job reclaims: 3
- Log retention: 7 days

Worker Configuration:
- Primary sources: Environment variables (REMOTE_HARNESS_URL, REMOTE_HARNESS_API_KEY)
- Secondary: Config file at ~/.config/remote-harness-worker/config.yaml
- Auto-generates worker ID from hostname + random suffix
- Auto-detects platform (linux/macos/windows/wsl)
- 30-second request timeout, 10-second connect timeout
- Bearer token authentication

Important: sqlx::migrate!("./migrations") embeds migrations at compile time - they're baked into the binary, no need to copy migration files to runtime image.

SQL queries use runtime sqlx::query() (not compile-time macros like query!()), so no SQLX_OFFLINE mode or running database needed at compile time.

Server does NOT serve static files - web UI is a standalone SPA.

=== FILES CREATED ===

1. Dockerfile (repo root) - Multi-stage build:
   - Stage 1 (rust-builder): rust:1.87-bookworm base, copies Cargo workspace manifests first for layer caching, creates stub files, pre-builds dependencies, then copies actual source and builds release binaries
   - Stage 2 (web-builder): node:20-alpine base, npm ci, npm run build
   - Stage 3 (server-runtime): debian:bookworm-slim, copies server binary, installs libssl3/ca-certificates/curl, exposes port 3000
   - Stage 4 (worker-runtime): debian:bookworm-slim, copies worker binary, installs libssl3/ca-certificates/git
   - Stage 5 (cli-runtime): debian:bookworm-slim, copies cli binary

2. web/Dockerfile - Two-stage: node:20-alpine builder (npm ci + build), nginx:alpine runtime serving /usr/share/nginx/html

3. web/nginx.conf - nginx config for SPA: try_files fallback to index.html, cache static assets 1y, no-cache index.html

4. .dockerignore - Excludes target/, web/node_modules/, web/dist/, .git/, .env files, logs/, plan/, docs/, *.md

5. web/.dockerignore - Excludes node_modules/, dist/, .env files

6. .env.example - Template with all environment variables: API_KEY, API_KEYS, POSTGRES_PASSWORD, POSTGRES_PORT, SERVER_PORT, CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS, WORKER_STALE_TIMEOUT_SECS, LOG_RETENTION_DAYS, WORKER_LABELS, POLL_INTERVAL_SECS, HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_SECS, WEB_PORT, RUST_LOG

