=== DECISIONS & NOTES ===

1. Used debian:bookworm-slim instead of alpine for Rust binaries - better compatibility with dynamically linked libraries (libssl, etc.)

2. Did NOT copy migrations to server runtime image because sqlx::migrate!() embeds them at compile time.

3. Added curl to server runtime for Docker healthcheck (curl -sf http://localhost:3000/health).

4. Web UI served via separate nginx container (web/Dockerfile) rather than from the server, since the server doesn't have static file serving built in.

5. Worker correctly fails when no API key is set - this is the expected behavior, not a bug. Users need to set API_KEY in .env file.

6. The Dockerfile uses a dependency caching strategy: copy Cargo.toml/lock first, create stub source files, pre-build dependencies, then copy actual source. This means dependency layer is cached unless Cargo.toml/lock change.

7. The .dockerignore excludes target/ to avoid sending the large build cache to the Docker daemon.

